# Nano-RAG for Nanobot 🐈

A brutally lightweight, zero-dependency Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system, built for extreme constraint environments. 

Inspired by the HKUDS `nanobot` framework and the recent release of `LightRAG v1.4`.

## The Problem
Enterprise RAG systems (like LightRAG's MiniRAG) are powerful but rely on heavy libraries (`scipy`, `networkx`, Graph DBs). If you are deploying an AI agent on a $10/mo Railway node with 512MB RAM, these dependencies will crash your server (OOM).

## The Fix: Nano-RAG
I built this custom RAG layer to run my personal agent (AUM NEXUS) entirely from a Redmi smartphone. 

- **Pure Python:** ~190 lines of code. Zero external vector databases (No Chroma, No Neo4j).
- **Mathematical core:** Uses standard `math.sqrt` and `sum` for Cosine Similarity.
- **Embeddings:** Uses OpenRouter's `text-embedding-3-small` API (pennies per month).
- **Storage:** Simple local JSON index. 

## How it works
It parses local `.md` and `.json` memory files, chunks them, generates vectors via OpenRouter, and computes similarities locally in Python before injecting the top matches into the LLM prompt.

## Credit
Built by Sam Chapelais as a custom layer on top of the routing philosophy of [HKUDS Nanobot](https://github.com/HKUDS/nanobot). Intelligence is about density, not infrastructure bloat.
